// Gate-1b: integer divide-by-zero. The interpreter raises a clean DivByZero
// error (exit 1); the JIT now emits a divisor==0 guard branching to the cx_trap
// clean exit (Gate-1b0, exit 126) instead of the raw sdiv that trapped in
// hardware (STATUS_ILLEGAL_INSTRUCTION 0xC000001D). Both backends reject
// non-zero → convergent expected-fail PASS. The divisor is a variable so the
// zero reaches runtime. Width-general — see _t8/_t64 siblings.
a: t32 = 5
b: t32 = 0
print(a / b)
